caption: Inedible. I ordered two hot subs, mozzarella wedges, and two drinks. Delivery was quick. The drinks were missing. The wedges were overcooked and cold. Both subs were cold, soggy, greasy messes. I had to wash my hands and wipe my countertop after unwrapping them. $38 down the drain, plus fees and tip (not the courier's fault). New owners/managers have had time to settle in, and this doesn't even compare to the old Taylor Gourmet.
The best mozzarella wedges.
Got an Italian sub to go.  It was delicious.   Premium ingredients.
Glad to see you reopened. Great salads.
Heath Cookie Smacks
I was pleasantly surprised, at how fast, and helpful the staff was
Glad you are back!  You were missed!  Same great food!
Did not dine
Not just good food, but quickly made even if you are a walk in. Plus friendly staff.
Good food & Clean Establishment

Couldnt be happier they reopened this location considering I stop in about once a week for lunch. Can easily be considered one of the best sandwich options in the area. The roast beef and chicken cutlet sandwiches can make or break a spot like this. Luckily Taylor knocks theirs out of the park.

First let's start with the customer service...Phenomenal! Kenneth and the young sister who was calling the names, was hands down great. I would hire them if I owned my own business regardless of type. The food was fast and delicious.  I am thankful that everyone else was closed today as it made me stop in. I will be back!
Fantastic to have it back, love the cheesesteaks!
They're back amd same as before. Good sandwiches, nice that you can get a regular or large.

Pretty decent reincarnation of the Taylor Gourmet of old. Sandwich menu is pretty much the same as under its previous ownership, and they're still pretty tasty and made quickly once you arrive. Online ordering helps speed things up too if that's your jam. I'm hoping they plan to continue expanding elsewhere in the city if this location remains successful!

I just went to Taylor Gourmet DC and the cheesesteak is sooo delicious and the risotto balls are out of this world.  The customer service is GREAT -- London, the cashier, was extremely nice.  I love the atmosphere.  Don't ever close your doors again!!!
Very delicious!

Taylor's is back! The last time I had Taylor Gourmet was when I was traveling through DCA.  I ordered the Cherry Street sub for pickup at their Pennsylvania Avenue location. Both the location and the food is the same as I remember. The food was fresh and tasted great, and the menu remains mostly the same as it did before.  I'd really like to see the Taylor Gourmet app come back. As someone who orders almost exclusively for pickup having a stamp card is really inconvenient.  Looking forward to returning again soon.
Closed!
Decent for a quick bite. Prices may make you swoon
Obama's favorite, and mine!

Great atmosphere! The cheese steak hoagie with provolone and mushrooms is delicious. It's filled with meat and flavor. The ladies working 8/31/18 were friendly, helpful, and provided exceptional service. One even assisted me with updating my info so that I could utilize Level Up app. Thank you for making my visit a wonderful experience.
Amazing sandwiches and sides. You have endless choices of excellent food.
Great cheese steak!
Great service, food and interier! It was the best burger I ever eat
Great service. Fast - but gets a bit too crowded. Sandwiches are great.

We came in with a group of 7 people on a Sunday. This place was one of the only shops open in the area & we were very hungry after walking the National Mall. It turned out to be a serious disappointment. Every sandwich served to our group was on bread that was incredibly difficult to eat.. maybe it was stale/old/overcooked? Most of us didn't even eat half our sandwiches. On top of the bad sandwiches, the seating was very uncomfortable & prices were really steep for a sandwich shop too. We spent well over $100 for these sandwiches. If we weren't so hungry and tired, I would have asked for a full refund and walked out. I cannot recommend this sandwich shop to anyone.
Great place, great prices :-)
Quick, friendly, and delicious. Excellent seasonal menu and five star customer service!

I'm a South Philly native and I can say the Taylor Gourmet's 9th Street hoagie is a true and delicious Philly Italian hoagie. If anything, perhaps on the gourmet end (delicious sharp provolone rather then the more bland slicing kind), but then look at the name of the establishment.

Randomly stopped in for lunch and glad I did. Great sandwiches with fresh ingredients and also reasonably priced for how much you get. It's the only alternative to a NYC bodega sandwich around DC that I know about.
Good food, good service, great selection of local products.
Had the cheese steak. It was good. Wish they had a better system for getting orders to customers, though.
Nice service and fresh ingredients.
Dry bread, weird tasting sub. I prefer Jimmy John's or Subway
Not bad, but every lunch in DC is 10 bucks anyway.
Great place for a sandwich or salad. I had the Cheesesteak Number 2 with beef. Love the Puck’s black cherry soda  with a splash of vanilla cream. Easy to miss but hard to forget. Good wait staff.
#1 is everything
Good sandwich and nicely located, although the lack of tap water is regretful
Reliable lunch spot, I don't think I've had anything I wasn't a fan of here. Service is pretty quick and the sodas are delicious too.
Great bread! I haven't had a bad sandwich there yet.
if you love sandwiches this is worth checking out.
Never had a bad sandwich there yet. Consistently great food with fresh ingredients and quality bread. I do wish they had fries however.
Very delicious food exelent service and always clean place. The restrooms are big and clean they always looks good. The crews are alway polite and very helpful.
Absolutely delicious.  Quick and convenient too

Food was actually pretty good, but service was awful. The cashier was extremely rude. Snapped at customers when they were sitting in places that she was planning on moving furniture to, propped the door open when it was freezing cold trying to freeze everyone out of the restaurant (even after someone in our party closed the door), had headphones in the whole time, and also told another customer there was no where to sit because she already put up all the chairs. Sad to say we will never go back even though the hoagies were good.

Taylor Gourmet, in Washington DC, is a nice place, good Food and good prices, one can place Order Online, they provide catering too, few choices: Italian turkey and vegetarian sandwiches. Chicken ,pork, cheese steak, salads is some of the choices for a good meal. They have few location's in Virginia , Washington DC, Maryland .

This has grown to be one of my favorite places for lunch. Prices are comparable to what you'd spend at most quick service restaurants around the DC Metro ($12-15 for a full meal). Their sandwiches are delicious, the boutiquey sodas at the fountain are amazing and they are pretty darn fast at getting customers in and out, whether you order ahead or walk in. Try one of the philly's (they have a #1 and a #2) and the heath cookies.
All of the chicken cutlet sandwiches are delicious
DC institution, great sandwiches. My favorite spot for lunch. They are known for their sandwiches made with chicken cutlets, but the risotto balls are amazing too!
So good. I went at lunch and was really impressed how fast the line moved. And of course the sandwiches are fantastic.
Great hoagies!!!
Solid sandwich shop with vegetarian options that were tasty and filling. Stopped in on a whim and was pleasantly surprised. Cool decor.

Staff was very pleasant. The chicken salad sandwich unfortunately was awful. The worst version of a prepacked chicken salad sold in a low end supermarket, I threw half of it out eventually, after forcing myself to eat some because it was the only lunch I had. Would never get chicken at any Taylor location and will not be returning to this location.
Get the cheese steak!
Great tasting sandwiches at this extremely crowded high paced sub shop. Seating is limited so take out is your best bet.
The food here is incredible. Unique and flavorful.
Sandwiches are delicious!! Love the Federal.

I really enjoyed my sandwich, I ordered one of their seasonal sandwiches the Gaucho Marx. My husband ordered the Ben Franklin. My problem was after asking me a few times what I wanted on the side, I still didn't get it! Even though he said okay, and he was the manager! Also they don't have the ginger ale anymore, but it's cool because they still have the cream soda!
Went in for a very quick lunch on a Friday and was in and out within 20 min. That's even including sitting down to eat the delicious Cheese Steak sandwich I ordered.
Decent food.
Great sandwiches that range from unique and adventurous to simple and delicious.
Love the sandwiches especially the Vine and their seasonal risotto balls are always amazing.  I suggest ordering ahead and picking it up because it can be very crowded at lunch.
I've had many of these sandwiches and all of them are amazing.

A great location for Taylor that rakes in business. Expect crowds at lunch hours. Food is good and service is fast, plus outdoor seating on Pennsylvania Ave and proximity to monuments make it a good pit-stop for tourists and businessmen alike. Try to come during off hours.
It is rare to find a good Pennsylvania hoagie in DC, but Taylor made it happen.
Great cheese steak

We needed a quick lunch near the White House - on a Sunday - and stumbled into Taylor Gourmet. The sandwiches were very creative: flavor combinations I've never seen before - and very tasty. Prices were reasonable. Service was friendly and quick. Currently being renovated so the ambience was a bit dusty, but that is being fixed.
Great service and food!

I am a fan of the Wilson salad; however I was very disappointed in the recent change in their salad container.  The new container has affected the taste and appeal of your salads.  Please go back to the original container.

Fantastic sandwiches, I really enjoy the federal and their fountain sodas are a nice change of pace.  Friendly and fast service but can get very busy around lunchtime.  I particularly like their app for the ease of payment and rewards.
We enjoyed the Federal and Turkey sandwiches. Neat place in a good location near the White House.
A glorified Subway.
Yum yum yum. A favorite for office catering.
Eh, good but not worth it
Damn good cheesesteak, and the italian cuts are solid as well. You're missing out if you don't get the South though - seldom do we find a sandwich like that.
Great food, pretty quick, waiting area is a little tight at lunch.
Wonderful gourmet sandwiches.. lovely cookies (one with toffee is really yummy)!
Love love love there sandwiches. Some if the best in DC. I go often and the special sandwiches are always with trying. Highly recommend.
Delicious sandwich, the place to go for lunch. There is sometimes a line, but the sandwiches are worth it.. Check it out if you are in the area.

I have never been disappointed at Taylor's. It's delicious. Great sandwiches, with a solid menu of salads and other items to pick from. Their ingredients are always fresh, and it isn't over priced. This location does a great job handling the lunch rush. You can pay with their ap and order ahead of time which are nice if you're a frequent customer.
